ratings.rComments: There was no leadership in the class, he does nothing to guide the discussion. He's useless. To use a phrase from his favorite topic: He started the boat and then jumped. When he made the point of no laptops in class, the class revolted and he gave in. I think we got some respect from him and he enjoyed a beer with us after the last class.

He thinks really highly of himself and he thinks his class is the most important thing in your life. Although the material is easy, the tests are unnecessarily hard because he phrases questions like SAT questions. You are also forced to go to his boring lecture to get the iclicker points.
Easy class but extremely boring

Most stuck up arrogant professor I have had at uiuc.. starts every class by a slide telling people to turn off cell phones Pauses randomly during lecture if there is any noise at all  and  just stands there wasting everyones time. yells at people before exams if they have hat on (seriously raises voice)..exams dnt start for 20 min into exam period

Difficulty of this class is overblown. I am not a business major but this is one of the easiest classes ever. The material is pretty common sense stuff. Exams will only appear tricky if you don't study at all.That said Preis is grumpy at times.And the only reason why someone might attend the boring lectures is because of the silly clicker points

I-Clicker points make attending lecture almost mandatory.Since material is relatively interesting though you won't fall sleep during class.Useless activities as well but the silver lining is that you get 25% outside of the tests.These are hard because there is a lot of stuff and some of the questions,it seems, are deliberately phrased to trick you

I only took this class because he was the only one teaching it. His exams are very hard, and not from his lectures. Lot of readings to do (articles,textbooks,lecture notes). Lots of useless Pre-class activities that I don't understand why they have only one attempt. Not sure if it was always like this, but the TAs are lot irritating too.
EXAMS ARE NOT REFLECTING WHAT HE TAUGHT...
Very boring, very stuck up.  No one likes going to his class.
Just a grumpy old guy. Just as 'difficult' as BA 310. If you read, you'll be more than fine.
One of the bad professors that you can't even avoid at U of I. Very nagging. He told us there would be no iclicker questions for the next class but he lied. Exams are pretty hard.

Tries to keep students paying attention with clicker questions.  Develops his own classroom distractions when he calls out people texting or on their laptops.  Very intelligent and friendly if you interact with him personally.  Exams are challenging but some questions are worded awkwardly.

Also, forgot to mention that he is the type of teacher who likes to gloat about his accomplishments. I.E.: "When I was in business" "I worked in consulting." And anyone who's been in his class knows about his desire of boating. He even used it as an example of "services mix" in the lecture when he mentioned some East Marine boating school.

Terrible professor.  Managed to make interesting material extremely boring.  Called out kids for talking just to embarass them.  Unfortunately you have to go to class for clicker points.  Exams were pretty difficult.  Too bad he's the only professor for this class.

One of the real awful professors you will ever run across at U of I. He is a smart guy but that unfortunately takes a backseat to his pissy attitude. He is a control freak basically. If 2 people are talking or texting or you try to open your test early, he will call them out.And for how much material there is, he makes the tests fairly challenging.

Smart dude, if you started your own company and went to Harvard you would mention it too. I missed a bunch of classes and still got over full credit, the trick is to look at the slide he JUST COVERED and answer them correctly. Don't ask questions like "How hard is the test from 1-10?" He'll rightfully make you feel like an idiot.
Go to class for the clickers but he makes the material harder than it should be.  he is also very arrogant

I have never dealt with a more disrespectful professor. Disregards his students' legitimate questions and makes everyone in the class feel like they are unimportant. Which is odd since the students are in fact paying his salary. At least the class is easy, even with the pointless clickers.

class is a piece of cake. I dominated this class despite being a dumbass. just read the lecture notes and scan the definitions in the book and you'll do good. also, he's one of those guys who will stop the entire class and embarass you if you're using a laptop not for class or sees you texting. weirdo.

Clickers are a waste because they make you go to class. Lecture's so boring as he spends forever talking about the most simple things. The HWs are pointless, but easy. His exams are strange because he oftens puts more than one correct answer so you have to guess which is the "best answer", which is pretty subjective. About 2 Qs per exam on book.

For how easy the material is, this class is inexplicably boring. Prof curved the class by 12 points b/c of how difficult his exams ended up being. Preis is not very captivating, and clicker points are a pain. Good luck!

Great Prof. Great class. The key to this class is knowing that he writes his tests in a way that makes you apply what you learned in lecture. I found this out the hard way. You have to study in a different way.

Great Professor! I totally do not agree with the posts here. I know other students who think he is an awesome Prof! He uses his own past business experience to support class lectures. Very cool dude! This class covers a ton of marketing terms, so it is a fast ride. Tests are difficult because he makes you apply what you have learned in class.
Horrible, horrible, teacher. Easily the most boring person in the world.
Boring lecture.  Takes a long time to cover material that could be covered quickly.  Tests are more common sense than anything else.

Decent class. Make sure and read the book for his tests because he takes about 20% of his questions from there. Lecture mandatory for "clicker points". 5 very easy homework assignments. Be sure and study a lot for the test, but there is not much work required other than that.

Hes boring and really uptight. If you're late 10 seconds to class he refuses to collect homework if its due. He also has the TAs spying around like vulchers when iclicker questions are up to make sure people aren't clicking someone else's iclicker. He thinks he is the sweetest thing, but would be an okay teacher if he'd just chill out.

this guy's class is terrible.  first, he's the most self-righteous, boring prof i've ever had a class with.  he has an entire page in the syllabus telling us how smart he is because of his engineering degree and how cool he is because he loves to sail the ocean blue.  but when it comes down to it, within 5 seconds you'll realize he is worthless
Horrible class but you have to take it if you're a business major.  He's extremely boring and the class is useless.  The only bright side is that it's easy.

His lectures are not very good. He does not answer questions well, and instead tries to awkwardly change the subject back to the lecture when he cannot answer a question. As many have said before, I would have never gone to lecture if it wasn't for the clicker questions. Tests are fairly straightforward, though.

Awful teacher...awful class...he never responds to student e-mails and does not make very good points in lecture. He seriously needs help with proofreading on his test, since the questions are IMPOSSIBLE to understand, he writes in broken english. His clicker questions waste over half the class-time. Don't take his class unless ABSOLUTELY necessary

His lectures are long, but his material is up-to-date with relevant examples.  Hundreds (literally) of clicker questions, so count on going to class.  A lot of his tests turn subjective material into an objective question.  No matter if you study or not - you'll never get them.  Easy B+
No Comments

ultimate struggle of a class, the only reason in hell you go to class is because of those damm clickers. he's unsure of himself and messes up CONSTANTLY. if there is another professor you're probably better of with anyone else

He was an awful teacher.  I fell asleep within two minutes of hitting the chairs because he was so boring.  The first test was so easy that I could have gotten an A on it in 5th grade.  He overcompensated by then making the second and third ones really hard.

Rough class if you don't go to take notes and stuff. People say just give your clicker to someone, but unless you're also going to find a dope who will take notes for you you're out of luck. Exams semi-difficult, impossible if you don't memorize your notes.

He makes his exams harder than it should be.  Class is pretty boring but you gotta go for clicker points unless you can find someone to go in for you.  It sucks how he makes you buy the class lecture notes and tells you to subscribe to the WSJ even though there's a free version from the business library.

michael preis, well besides that i created him as my driver in nascar '06, he's not all that great, the class lasts 80 minutes when it could last 8, he tells outrageous stories about how he invented ski racks for porsches, and he has no clue how to use a computer, horrible class, give your clicker to somebody so you don't have to attend

This class shouldn't be hard but with Preis, it is. He makes his exams totally unrelated to class material. He doesn't give out study guides. And there are no plus or minuses used in the class. If you can avoid taking it with him, do it.

Professor Preis is just awful - he is so incredibly boring but you are forced to go to his class to get clicker points.  His exams aren't too difficult - just read the class notes beforehand.  There are only 3 exams during the semester plus online homework and loads of extra credit.  Do all of the extra credit!  Overall, this class is an easy A.
The materials taught in class is not related to what's on the exam. Watch out~
